  <h1>üìù How to Make a Table on TI-84 Plus (Super Simple Guide)</h1>
  <p>The Table feature on the TI-84 Plus is one of the fastest ways to see how a function behaves. Whether you‚Äôre graphing, checking homework, or just exploring math, a table shows instant x‚Äìy values for any equation you enter.</p>
  <p>This guide walks you step by step in a clean, human-friendly format that anyone can follow‚Äîeven beginners.</p>

  <!-- Table of Contents -->
  <nav class="toc" aria-label="Article table of contents">
    <h3>Quick Navigation</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#step1">Step 1: Enter Your Function</a></li>
      <li><a href="#step2">Step 2: Open the Table</a></li>
      <li><a href="#step3">Step 3: Adjust Table Settings</a></li>
      <li><a href="#step4">Step 4: AUTO vs ASK Mode</a></li>
      <li><a href="#step5">Step 5: Editing or Clearing a Function</a></li>
      <li><a href="#step6">Step 6: What You Can Do With the Table</a></li>
      <li><a href="#step7">Step 7: Practice Using Our Online TI-84</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <!-- Step 1 -->
  <div class="step-card" id="step1">
    <h3>Step 1: Enter Your Function in the Y= Menu</h3>
    <p>Before you can see a table, you need to enter a function:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Press <strong>Y=</strong></li>
      <li>Move to <strong>Y1</strong></li>
      <li>Type your function (example: <code>x^2 + 3x</code>)</li>
      <li>Press <strong>ENTER</strong></li>
      <li>You can enter multiple functions in <strong>Y2, Y3</strong>, etc. The table will display all of them automatically.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 2 -->
  <div class="step-card" id="step2">
    <h3>Step 2: Open the Table</h3>
    <p>To see your function values:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Press <strong>2ND</strong></li>
      <li>Press <strong>GRAPH</strong> (this opens <strong>TABLE</strong>)</li>
      <li>You‚Äôll see x-values on the left and the corresponding y-values on the right.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 3 -->
  <div class="step-card" id="step3">
    <h3>Step 3: Adjust the Table Settings (TblStart & ŒîTbl)</h3>
    <p>Control how your table behaves:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Press <strong>2ND</strong> then <strong>WINDOW</strong> (opens <strong>TBLSET</strong>)</li>
      <li><strong>TblStart</strong>: set where the table begins (0, -10, etc.)</li>
      <li><strong>ŒîTbl</strong>: step size for x-values (1 = standard, 0.1 = fine, 5 = large)</li>
      <li>After adjusting, press <strong>TABLE</strong> again to see updated values.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 4 -->
  <div class="step-card" id="step4">
    <h3>Step 4: AUTO vs ASK Mode</h3>
    <p>Decide how x-values are entered:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>AUTO:</strong> Calculator fills x-values automatically (ideal for most students)</li>
      <li><strong>ASK:</strong> You type x-values manually. Great for specific points like x = 2.5</li>
      <li>To use ASK mode: switch Indpnt ‚Üí ASK, press TABLE, type x-value, press ENTER</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 5 -->
  <div class="step-card" id="step5">
    <h3>Step 5: Editing or Clearing a Function</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Press <strong>Y=</strong></li>
      <li>Press <strong>CLEAR</strong> on the old function</li>
      <li>Type your new equation</li>
      <li>Return to <strong>TABLE</strong> to see the updated table</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 6 -->
  <div class="step-card" id="step6">
    <h3>Step 6: What You Can Do With the TI-84 Table</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>‚úî Find roots of functions (look for y-values near 0)</li>
      <li>‚úî Check homework answers quickly</li>
      <li>‚úî Compare multiple functions side by side (Y1 vs Y2)</li>
      <li>‚úî Explore patterns in algebra, sequences, and graphs</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The table is simple but powerful ‚Äî use it to understand any function better.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 7 -->
  <div class="step-card" id="step7">
    <h3>Step 7: Practice Using Our TI-84 Online Calculator</h3>
    <p>Follow every step above using our free online version ‚Äî no physical calculator needed:</p>
    <p>üëâ <a href="https://mycalculatorpal.com/ti84-calculator" target="_blank">Try the TI-84 Online Now</a></p>
  </div>

  <!-- Smooth Scroll + Highlight Script -->
  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.blog a').forEach(link => {
      link.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
        const href = this.getAttribute('href') || '';
        if (!href.startsWith('#')) return;
        const targetId = href.substring(1);
        const target = document.getElementById(targetId);
        if (target) {
          e.preventDefault();
          target.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'center' });
          target.classList.add('highlighted');
          setTimeout(() => target.classList.remove('highlighted'), 1500);
        }
      });
    });
  </script>
